HEADWORD: Axil
<hw>Ax"il</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧ks"⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>axilla</ets>. Cf. <er>Axle</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
angle or point of divergence between the upper side of a branch, leaf,
or petiole, and the stem or branch from which it springs.</def>
